No.	            String	                         StringBuffer

1)	String class is immutable.	            StringBuffer class is mutable.

2)	String is slow and consumes             StringBuffer is fast and consumes less memory when you cancat strings.
    more memory when you concat
    too many strings because 
    every time it creates new 
    instance.	
    
3)	String class overrides the              StringBuffer class doesn't override the equals() method of Object class.
    equals() method of Object class. 
    So you can compare the contents
    of two strings by equals() method.	 